{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"How do groups get anything done? Right?"},{"time":3000,"text":"How do you organize a group of individuals"},{"time":5000,"text":"so that the output of the group"},{"time":7000,"text":"is something coherent and of lasting value,"},{"time":9000,"text":"instead of just being chaos?"},{"time":11000,"text":"And the economic framing of that problem"},{"time":14000,"text":"is called coordination costs."},{"time":16000,"text":"And a coordination cost is essentially all of the financial"},{"time":20000,"text":"or institutional difficulties in arranging group output."},{"time":24000,"text":"And we've had a classic answer for coordination costs,"},{"time":27000,"text":"which is, if you want to coordinate the work of a group of people,"},{"time":30000,"text":"you start an institution, right? You raise some resources."},{"time":32000,"text":"You found something. It can be private or public."},{"time":35000,"text":"It can be for profit or not profit. It can be large or small."},{"time":38000,"text":"But you get these resources together."},{"time":40000,"text":"You found an institution, and you use the institution"},{"time":43000,"text":"to coordinate the activities of the group."}]},{"cues":[{"time":45000,"text":"More recently, because the cost of letting groups"},{"time":49000,"text":"communicate with each other has fallen through the floor --"},{"time":52000,"text":"and communication costs are one of the big"},{"time":54000,"text":"inputs to coordination -- there has been a second answer,"},{"time":58000,"text":"which is to put the cooperation into the infrastructure,"},{"time":62000,"text":"to design systems that coordinate the output"},{"time":65000,"text":"of the group as a by-product of the operating of the system,"},{"time":68000,"text":"without regard to institutional models."},{"time":71000,"text":"So, that's what I want to talk about today."},{"time":73000,"text":"I'm going to illustrate it with some fairly concrete examples,"},{"time":75000,"text":"but always pointing to the broader themes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79000,"text":"So, I'm going to start by trying to answer a question"},{"time":81000,"text":"that I know each of you will have asked yourself at some point or other,"},{"time":83000,"text":"and which the Internet is purpose-built to answer,"},{"time":85000,"text":"which is, where can I get a picture of a roller-skating mermaid?"},{"time":89000,"text":"So, in New York City, on the first Saturday of every summer,"},{"time":93000,"text":"Coney Island, our local, charmingly run-down amusement park,"},{"time":96000,"text":"hosts the Mermaid Parade. It's an amateur parade;"},{"time":99000,"text":"people come from all over the city; people get all dressed up."},{"time":102000,"text":"Some people get less dressed up."},{"time":104000,"text":"Young and old, dancing in the streets."},{"time":107000,"text":"Colorful characters, and a good time is had by all."},{"time":110000,"text":"And what I want to call your attention to is not the Mermaid Parade itself,"},{"time":112000,"text":"charming though it is, but rather to these photos."},{"time":115000,"text":"I didn't take them. How did I get them?"},{"time":118000,"text":"And the answer is: I got them from Flickr."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120000,"text":"Flickr is a photo-sharing service"},{"time":123000,"text":"that allows people to take photos, upload them,"},{"time":125000,"text":"share them over the Web and so forth."},{"time":126000,"text":"Recently, Flickr has added an additional function called tagging."},{"time":130000,"text":"Tagging was pioneered by Delicious and Joshua Schachter."},{"time":133000,"text":"Delicious is a social bookmarking service."},{"time":135000,"text":"Tagging is a cooperative infrastructure answer to classification."},{"time":140000,"text":"Right? If I had given this talk last year,"},{"time":143000,"text":"I couldn't do what I just did,"},{"time":145000,"text":"because I couldn't have found those photos."},{"time":147000,"text":"But instead of saying,"},{"time":149000,"text":"we need to hire a professional class of librarians"},{"time":151000,"text":"to organize these photos once they're uploaded,"},{"time":153000,"text":"Flickr simply turned over to the users"},{"time":156000,"text":"the ability to characterize the photos."},{"time":158000,"text":"So, I was able to go in and draw down photos that had been tagged"},{"time":161000,"text":"\"Mermaid Parade.\" There were 3,100 photos taken by 118 photographers,"},{"time":167000,"text":"all aggregated and then put under this nice, neat name,"},{"time":170000,"text":"shown in reverse chronological order."},{"time":172000,"text":"And I was then able to go and retrieve them"},{"time":174000,"text":"to give you that little slideshow."}]},{"cues":[{"time":176000,"text":"Now, what hard problem is being solved here?"},{"time":179000,"text":"And it's -- in the most schematic possible view,"},{"time":181000,"text":"it's a coordination problem, right?"},{"time":183000,"text":"There are a large number of people on the Internet,"},{"time":185000,"text":"a very small fraction of them have photos of the Mermaid Parade."},{"time":189000,"text":"How do we get those people together to contribute that work?"},{"time":193000,"text":"The classic answer is to form an institution, right?"},{"time":196000,"text":"To draw those people into some prearranged structure"},{"time":200000,"text":"that has explicit goals."},{"time":202000,"text":"And I want to call your attention to"},{"time":204000,"text":"some of the side effects of going the institutional route."}]},{"cues":[{"time":209000,"text":"First of all, when you form an institution,"},{"time":211000,"text":"you take on a management problem, right?"},{"time":213000,"text":"No good just hiring employees,"},{"time":215000,"text":"you also have to hire other employees to manage those employees"},{"time":218000,"text":"and to enforce the goals of the institution and so forth."},{"time":221000,"text":"Secondly, you have to bring structure into place."},{"time":224000,"text":"Right? You have to have economic structure."},{"time":226000,"text":"You have to have legal structure."},{"time":228000,"text":"You have to have physical structure."},{"time":229000,"text":"And that creates additional costs."},{"time":232000,"text":"Third, forming an institution is inherently exclusionary."},{"time":236000,"text":"You notice we haven't got everybody who has a photo."},{"time":240000,"text":"You can't hire everyone in a company, right?"},{"time":243000,"text":"You can't recruit everyone into a governmental organization."},{"time":246000,"text":"You have to exclude some people."},{"time":248000,"text":"And fourth, as a result of that exclusion,"},{"time":250000,"text":"you end up with a professional class. Look at the change here."},{"time":254000,"text":"We've gone from people with photos to photographers."},{"time":257000,"text":"Right? We've created a professional class of photographers"},{"time":261000,"text":"whose goal is to go out and photograph the Mermaid Parade,"},{"time":263000,"text":"or whatever else they're sent out to photograph."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268000,"text":"When you build cooperation into the infrastructure,"},{"time":271000,"text":"which is the Flickr answer,"},{"time":274000,"text":"you can leave the people where they are"},{"time":276000,"text":"and you take the problem to the individuals, rather than"},{"time":280000,"text":"moving the individuals to the problem."},{"time":281000,"text":"You arrange the coordination in the group, and by doing that"},{"time":288000,"text":"you get the same outcome, without the institutional difficulties."},{"time":292000,"text":"You lose the institutional imperative."},{"time":294000,"text":"You lose the right to shape people's work when it's volunteer effort,"},{"time":297000,"text":"but you also shed the institutional cost,"},{"time":300000,"text":"which gives you greater flexibility."},{"time":302000,"text":"What Flickr does is it replaces planning with coordination."},{"time":307000,"text":"And this is a general aspect of these cooperative systems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310000,"text":"Right. You'll have experienced this in your life"},{"time":313000,"text":"whenever you bought your first mobile phone,"},{"time":315000,"text":"and you stopped making plans."},{"time":317000,"text":"You just said, \"I'll call you when I get there.\""},{"time":319000,"text":"\"Call me when you get off work.\" Right?"},{"time":321000,"text":"That is a point-to-point replacement of coordination with planning."},{"time":326000,"text":"Right. We're now able to do that kind of thing with groups."},{"time":330000,"text":"To say instead of, we must make an advance plan,"},{"time":333000,"text":"we must have a five-year projection"},{"time":334000,"text":"of where the Wikipedia is going to be, or whatever,"},{"time":337000,"text":"you can just say, let's coordinate the group effort,"},{"time":340000,"text":"and let's deal with it as we go,"},{"time":342000,"text":"because we're now well-enough coordinated"},{"time":343000,"text":"that we don't have to take on the problems of deciding in advance what to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348000,"text":"So here's another example. This one's somewhat more somber."},{"time":351000,"text":"These are photos on Flickr tagged \"Iraq.\""},{"time":357000,"text":"And everything that was hard about the coordination cost"},{"time":360000,"text":"with the Mermaid Parade is even harder here."},{"time":363000,"text":"There are more pictures. There are more photographers."},{"time":366000,"text":"It's taken over a wider geographic area."},{"time":370000,"text":"The photos are spread out over a longer period of time."},{"time":372000,"text":"And worst of all, that figure at the bottom,"},{"time":376000,"text":"approximately ten photos per photographer, is a lie."},{"time":380000,"text":"It's mathematically true,"},{"time":382000,"text":"but it doesn't really talk about anything important --"},{"time":384000,"text":"because in these systems, the average isn't really what matters."}]},{"cues":[{"time":389000,"text":"What matters is this."},{"time":391000,"text":"This is a graph of photographs tagged Iraq"},{"time":396000,"text":"as taken by the 529 photographers who contributed the 5,445 photos."},{"time":402000,"text":"And it's ranked in order of number of photos taken per photographer."},{"time":407000,"text":"You can see here, over at the end,"},{"time":409000,"text":"our most prolific photographer has taken around 350 photos,"},{"time":413000,"text":"and you can see there's a few people who have taken hundreds of photos."},{"time":417000,"text":"Then there's dozens of people who've taken dozens of photos."},{"time":420000,"text":"And by the time we get around here,"},{"time":422000,"text":"we get ten or fewer photos, and then there's this long, flat tail."},{"time":426000,"text":"And by the time you get to the middle,"},{"time":428000,"text":"you've got hundreds of people"},{"time":430000,"text":"who have contributed only one photo each."}]},{"cues":[{"time":433000,"text":"This is called a power-law distribution."},{"time":435000,"text":"It appears often in unconstrained social systems"},{"time":440000,"text":"where people are allowed to contribute as much or as little as they like --"},{"time":444000,"text":"this is often what you get. Right?"},{"time":446000,"text":"The math behind the power-law distribution is that whatever's in the nth position"},{"time":450000,"text":"is doing about one-nth of whatever's being measured,"},{"time":453000,"text":"relative to the person in the first position."},{"time":455000,"text":"So, we'd expect the tenth most prolific photographer"},{"time":457000,"text":"to have contributed about a tenth of the photos,"},{"time":460000,"text":"and the hundredth most prolific photographer"},{"time":462000,"text":"to have contributed only about a hundred as many photos"},{"time":465000,"text":"as the most prolific photographer did."},{"time":467000,"text":"So, the head of the curve can be sharper or flatter."},{"time":471000,"text":"But that basic math accounts both for the steep slope"},{"time":473000,"text":"and for the long, flat tail."}]},{"cues":[{"time":475000,"text":"And curiously, in these systems, as they grow larger,"},{"time":478000,"text":"the systems don't converge; they diverge more."},{"time":482000,"text":"In bigger systems, the head gets bigger"},{"time":483000,"text":"and the tail gets longer, so the imbalance increases."},{"time":489000,"text":"You can see the curve is obviously heavily left-weighted. Here's how heavily:"},{"time":493000,"text":"if you take the top 10 percent of photographers contributing to this system,"},{"time":497000,"text":"they account for three quarters of the photos taken --"},{"time":501000,"text":"just the top 10 percent most prolific photographers."},{"time":504000,"text":"If you go down to five percent,"},{"time":506000,"text":"you're still accounting for 60 percent of the photos."},{"time":509000,"text":"If you go down to one percent, exclude 99 percent of the group effort,"},{"time":515000,"text":"you're still accounting for almost a quarter of the photos."},{"time":518000,"text":"And because of this left weighting,"},{"time":520000,"text":"the average is actually here, way to the left."},{"time":525000,"text":"And that sounds strange to our ears,"},{"time":527000,"text":"but what ends up happening is that 80 percent of the contributors"},{"time":530000,"text":"have contributed a below-average amount."},{"time":533000,"text":"That sounds strange because we expect average and middle"},{"time":535000,"text":"to be about the same, but they're not at all."}]},{"cues":[{"time":538000,"text":"This is the math underlying the 80/20 rule. Right?"},{"time":542000,"text":"Whenever you hear anybody talking about the 80/20 rule,"},{"time":544000,"text":"this is what's going on. Right?"},{"time":546000,"text":"20 percent of the merchandise accounts for 80 percent of the revenue,"},{"time":550000,"text":"20 percent of the users use 80 percent of the resources --"},{"time":552000,"text":"this is the shape people are talking about when that happens."},{"time":557000,"text":"Institutions only have two tools: carrots and sticks."},{"time":560000,"text":"And the 80 percent zone is a no-carrot and no-stick zone."},{"time":564000,"text":"The costs of running the institution mean that you cannot"},{"time":573000,"text":"take on the work of those people easily in an institutional frame."},{"time":576000,"text":"The institutional model always pushes leftwards,"},{"time":580000,"text":"treating these people as employees."},{"time":582000,"text":"The institutional response is,"},{"time":583000,"text":"I can get 75 percent of the value for 10 percent of the hires -- great,"},{"time":588000,"text":"that's what I'll do."},{"time":590000,"text":"The cooperative infrastructure model says,"},{"time":592000,"text":"why do you want to give up a quarter of the value?"},{"time":595000,"text":"If your system is designed"},{"time":597000,"text":"so that you have to give up a quarter of the value,"},{"time":600000,"text":"re-engineer the system."},{"time":603000,"text":"Don't take on the cost that prevents you"},{"time":605000,"text":"from getting to the contributions of these people."},{"time":607000,"text":"Build the system so that anybody can contribute at any amount."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612000,"text":"So the coordination response asks not,"},{"time":618000,"text":"how are these people as employees, but rather,"},{"time":621000,"text":"what is their contribution like? Right?"},{"time":623000,"text":"We have over here Psycho Milt, a Flickr user,"},{"time":626000,"text":"who has contributed one, and only one, photo titled \"Iraq.\""},{"time":631000,"text":"And here's the photo. Right. Labeled, \"Bad Day at Work.\""},{"time":635000,"text":"Right? So the question is,"},{"time":638000,"text":"do you want that photo? Yes or no."},{"time":641000,"text":"The question is not, is Psycho Milt a good employee?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":645000,"text":"And the tension here is between institution as enabler"},{"time":650000,"text":"and institution as obstacle."},{"time":652000,"text":"When you're dealing with the left-hand edge"},{"time":654000,"text":"of one of these distributions,"},{"time":656000,"text":"when you're dealing with the people who spend a lot of time"},{"time":658000,"text":"producing a lot of the material you want,"},{"time":660000,"text":"that's an institution-as-enabler world."},{"time":662000,"text":"You can hire those people as employees, you can coordinate their work"},{"time":665000,"text":"and you can get some output."},{"time":667000,"text":"But when you're down here, where the Psycho Milts of the world"},{"time":669000,"text":"are adding one photo at a time,"},{"time":672000,"text":"that's institution as obstacle."}]},{"cues":[{"time":675000,"text":"Institutions hate being told they're obstacles."},{"time":679000,"text":"One of the first things that happens"},{"time":681000,"text":"when you institutionalize a problem"},{"time":683000,"text":"is that the first goal of the institution"},{"time":687000,"text":"immediately shifts from whatever the nominal goal was"},{"time":689000,"text":"to self-preservation."},{"time":691000,"text":"And the actual goal of the institution goes to two through n."},{"time":695000,"text":"Right? So, when institutions are told they are obstacles,"},{"time":698000,"text":"and that there are other ways of coordinating the value,"},{"time":700000,"text":"they go through something a little bit like the Kubler-Ross stages --"},{"time":705000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":706000,"text":"-- of reaction, being told you have a fatal illness:"},{"time":708000,"text":"denial, anger, bargaining, acceptance."},{"time":712000,"text":"Most of the cooperative systems we've seen"},{"time":714000,"text":"haven't been around long enough"},{"time":715000,"text":"to have gotten to the acceptance phase."}]},{"cues":[{"time":718000,"text":"Many, many institutions are still in denial,"},{"time":720000,"text":"but we're seeing recently a lot of both anger and bargaining."},{"time":725000,"text":"There's a wonderful, small example going on right now."},{"time":727000,"text":"In France, a bus company is suing people for forming a carpool,"},{"time":732000,"text":"right, because the fact that they have coordinated"},{"time":735000,"text":"themselves to create cooperative value is depriving them of revenue."},{"time":741000,"text":"You can follow this in the Guardian."},{"time":742000,"text":"It's actually quite entertaining."}]},{"cues":[{"time":746000,"text":"The bigger question is,"},{"time":748000,"text":"what do you do about the value down here?"},{"time":751000,"text":"Right? How do you capture that?"},{"time":754000,"text":"And institutions, as I've said, are prevented from capturing that."},{"time":758000,"text":"Steve Ballmer, now CEO of Microsoft,"},{"time":760000,"text":"was criticizing Linux a couple of years ago, and he said,"},{"time":762000,"text":"\"Oh, this business of thousands of programmers"},{"time":764000,"text":"contributing to Linux, this is a myth."},{"time":766000,"text":"We've looked at who's contributed to Linux,"},{"time":769000,"text":"and most of the patches have been produced by programmers"},{"time":772000,"text":"who've only done one thing.\" Right?"},{"time":776000,"text":"You can hear this distribution under that complaint."},{"time":780000,"text":"And you can see why, from Ballmer's point of view,"},{"time":782000,"text":"that's a bad idea, right?"},{"time":783000,"text":"We hired this programmer, he came in, he drank our Cokes"},{"time":786000,"text":"and played Foosball for three years and he had one idea."},{"time":788000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":789000,"text":"Right? Bad hire. Right?"},{"time":792000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":794000,"text":"The Psycho Milt question is, was it a good idea?"},{"time":799000,"text":"What if it was a security patch?"},{"time":801000,"text":"What if it was a security patch for a buffer overflow exploit,"},{"time":805000,"text":"of which Windows has not some, [but] several?"},{"time":807000,"text":"Do you want that patch, right?"},{"time":811000,"text":"The fact that a single programmer can,"},{"time":813000,"text":"without having to move into a professional relation"},{"time":816000,"text":"to an institution, improve Linux once"},{"time":819000,"text":"and never be seen from again, should terrify Ballmer."},{"time":823000,"text":"Because this kind of value is unreachable in classic"},{"time":827000,"text":"institutional frameworks, but is part of cooperative"},{"time":829000,"text":"systems of open-source software, of file sharing,"}]},{"cues":[{"time":832000,"text":"of the Wikipedia. I've used a lot of examples from Flickr,"},{"time":835000,"text":"but there are actually stories about this from all over."},{"time":838000,"text":"Meetup, a service founded so that users could find people"},{"time":841000,"text":"in their local area who share their interests and affinities"},{"time":843000,"text":"and actually have a real-world meeting offline in a cafe"},{"time":847000,"text":"or a pub or what have you."},{"time":849000,"text":"When Scott Heiferman founded Meetup,"},{"time":851000,"text":"he thought it would be used for, you know,"},{"time":853000,"text":"train spotters and cat fanciers -- classic affinity groups."},{"time":855000,"text":"The inventors don't know what the invention is."},{"time":858000,"text":"Number one group on Meetup right now,"},{"time":860000,"text":"most chapters in most cities with most members, most active?"},{"time":863000,"text":"Stay-at-home moms. Right?"},{"time":865000,"text":"In the suburbanized, dual-income United States,"},{"time":868000,"text":"stay-at-home moms are actually missing"},{"time":871000,"text":"the social infrastructure that comes from extended family"},{"time":874000,"text":"and local, small-scale neighborhoods."},{"time":877000,"text":"So they're reinventing it, using these tools."},{"time":880000,"text":"Meetup is the platform,"},{"time":881000,"text":"but the value here is in social infrastructure."},{"time":884000,"text":"If you want to know what technology is going to change the world,"},{"time":887000,"text":"don't pay attention to 13-year-old boys --"},{"time":889000,"text":"pay attention to young mothers,"},{"time":891000,"text":"because they have got not an ounce of support for technology"},{"time":894000,"text":"that doesn't materially make their lives better."},{"time":897000,"text":"This is so much more important than Xbox,"},{"time":899000,"text":"but it's a lot less glitzy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":901000,"text":"I think this is a revolution."},{"time":903000,"text":"I think that this is a really profound change"},{"time":906000,"text":"in the way human affairs are arranged."},{"time":907000,"text":"And I use that word advisedly."},{"time":909000,"text":"It's a revolution in that it's a change in equilibrium."},{"time":912000,"text":"It's a whole new way of doing things, which includes new downsides."},{"time":918000,"text":"In the United States right now, a woman named Judith Miller"},{"time":921000,"text":"is in jail for not having given to a Federal Grand Jury her sources --"},{"time":926000,"text":"she's a reporter for the New York Times --"},{"time":927000,"text":"her sources, in a very abstract and hard-to-follow case."},{"time":930000,"text":"And journalists are in the street rallying to improve the shield laws."},{"time":933000,"text":"The shield laws are our laws -- pretty much a patchwork of state laws --"},{"time":937000,"text":"that prevent a journalist from having to betray a source."},{"time":940000,"text":"This is happening, however, against the background"},{"time":943000,"text":"of the rise of Web logging."},{"time":945000,"text":"Web logging is a classic example of mass amateurization."},{"time":949000,"text":"It has de-professionalized publishing."},{"time":951000,"text":"Want to publish globally anything you think today?"},{"time":954000,"text":"It is a one-button operation that you can do for free."},{"time":958000,"text":"That has sent the professional class of publishing down"},{"time":962000,"text":"into the ranks of mass amateurization."},{"time":965000,"text":"And so the shield law, as much as we want it --"},{"time":969000,"text":"we want a professional class of truth-tellers --"},{"time":971000,"text":"it is becoming increasingly incoherent, because"},{"time":974000,"text":"the institution is becoming incoherent."},{"time":976000,"text":"There are people in the States right now"},{"time":978000,"text":"tying themselves into knots, trying to figure out"},{"time":981000,"text":"whether or not bloggers are journalists."},{"time":983000,"text":"And the answer to that question is,"},{"time":985000,"text":"it doesn't matter, because that's not the right question."},{"time":988000,"text":"Journalism was an answer to an even more important question,"},{"time":992000,"text":"which is, how will society be informed?"},{"time":994000,"text":"How will they share ideas and opinions?"},{"time":997000,"text":"And if there is an answer to that that happens outside"},{"time":1000000,"text":"the professional framework of journalism,"},{"time":1002000,"text":"it makes no sense to take a professional metaphor"},{"time":1006000,"text":"and apply it to this distributed class."},{"time":1010000,"text":"So as much as we want the shield laws,"},{"time":1012000,"text":"the background -- the institution to which they were attached --"},{"time":1016000,"text":"is becoming incoherent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1018000,"text":"Here's another example."},{"time":1020000,"text":"Pro-ana, the pro-ana groups."},{"time":1022000,"text":"These are groups of teenage girls"},{"time":1024000,"text":"who have taken on Web logs, bulletin boards,"},{"time":1027000,"text":"other kinds of cooperative infrastructure,"},{"time":1029000,"text":"and have used it to set up support groups for"},{"time":1031000,"text":"remaining anorexic by choice."},{"time":1033000,"text":"They post pictures of thin models, which they call \"thinspiration.\""},{"time":1036000,"text":"They have little slogans, like \"Salvation through Starvation.\""},{"time":1039000,"text":"They even have Lance Armstrong-style bracelets,"},{"time":1041000,"text":"these red bracelets, which signify, in the small group,"},{"time":1044000,"text":"I am trying to maintain my eating disorder."},{"time":1047000,"text":"They trade tips, like, if you feel like eating something,"},{"time":1049000,"text":"clean a toilet or the litter box. The feeling will pass."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1054000,"text":"We're used to support groups being beneficial."},{"time":1057000,"text":"We have an attitude that support groups are inherently beneficial."},{"time":1060000,"text":"But it turns out that the logic of the support group is value neutral."},{"time":1064000,"text":"A support group is simply a small group that wants to maintain"},{"time":1068000,"text":"a way of living in the context of a larger group."},{"time":1071000,"text":"Now, when the larger group is a bunch of drunks,"},{"time":1073000,"text":"and the small group wants to stay sober, then we think,"},{"time":1075000,"text":"that's a great support group."},{"time":1077000,"text":"But when the small group is teenage girls"},{"time":1079000,"text":"who want to stay anorexic by choice, then we're horrified."},{"time":1083000,"text":"What's happened is that the normative goals"},{"time":1086000,"text":"of the support groups that we're used to,"},{"time":1088000,"text":"came from the institutions that were framing them,"},{"time":1091000,"text":"and not from the infrastructure."},{"time":1092000,"text":"Once the infrastructure becomes generically available,"},{"time":1096000,"text":"the logic of the support group has been revealed to be"},{"time":1098000,"text":"accessible to anyone, including people pursuing these kinds of goals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1103000,"text":"So, there are significant downsides to these changes"},{"time":1105000,"text":"as well as upsides. And of course, in the current environment,"},{"time":1108000,"text":"one need allude only lightly to the work of non-state actors"},{"time":1113000,"text":"trying to influence global affairs, and taking advantage of these."},{"time":1116000,"text":"This is a social map of the hijackers and their associates"},{"time":1119000,"text":"who perpetrated the 9/11 attack."},{"time":1123000,"text":"It was produced by analyzing their communications patterns"},{"time":1127000,"text":"using a lot of these tools. And doubtless the intelligence communities of the world"},{"time":1130000,"text":"are doing the same work today for the attacks of last week."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1134000,"text":"Now, this is the part of the talk where I tell you"},{"time":1136000,"text":"what's going to come as a result of all of this,"},{"time":1138000,"text":"but I'm running out of time, which is good,"},{"time":1141000,"text":"because I don't know."},{"time":1143000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1145000,"text":"Right. As with the printing press, if it's really a revolution,"},{"time":1149000,"text":"it doesn't take us from Point A to Point B."},{"time":1151000,"text":"It takes us from Point A to chaos."},{"time":1154000,"text":"The printing press precipitated 200 years of chaos,"},{"time":1159000,"text":"moving from a world where the Catholic Church"},{"time":1161000,"text":"was the sort of organizing political force to the Treaty of Westphalia,"},{"time":1165000,"text":"when we finally knew what the new unit was: the nation state."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1168000,"text":"Now, I'm not predicting 200 years of chaos as a result of this. 50."},{"time":1173000,"text":"50 years in which loosely coordinated groups"},{"time":1177000,"text":"are going to be given increasingly high leverage,"},{"time":1180000,"text":"and the more those groups forego traditional institutional imperatives --"},{"time":1184000,"text":"like deciding in advance what's going to happen,"},{"time":1187000,"text":"or the profit motive -- the more leverage they'll get."},{"time":1190000,"text":"And institutions are going to come under"},{"time":1192000,"text":"an increasing degree of pressure,"},{"time":1194000,"text":"and the more rigidly managed, and the more they rely"},{"time":1196000,"text":"on information monopolies, the greater the pressure is going to be."},{"time":1200000,"text":"And that's going to happen one arena at a time,"},{"time":1202000,"text":"one institution at a time. The forces are general,"},{"time":1205000,"text":"but the results are going to be specific."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1207000,"text":"And so the point here is not,"},{"time":1209000,"text":"\"This is wonderful,\" or \"We're going to see a transition"},{"time":1212000,"text":"from only institutions to only cooperative framework.\""},{"time":1215000,"text":"It's going to be much more complicated than that."},{"time":1217000,"text":"But the point is that it's going to be a massive readjustment."},{"time":1220000,"text":"And since we can see it in advance and know it's coming,"},{"time":1222000,"text":"my argument is essentially: we might as well get good at it."},{"time":1225000,"text":"Thank you very much."},{"time":1227000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}